column6: The top marker genes for cluster_3, including IL7R, NGFRAP1, RGCC, ZNF141, RPS29, PILRB, PASK, PDCD4-AS1, C14orf64, and DENND2D, suggest that this cluster most likely represents memory T cells. IL7R (Interleukin-7 receptor alpha) is notably expressed on memory T cells, playing a crucial role in their survival and homeostasis. ([en.wikipedia.org](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Memory_T_cell?utm_source=openai))
